	<item>
		<title>FrE Private Message is an extension of FreelanceEngine. With it, your employers can easily start a private conversation with bidders before accepting the bid. Thus, they can understand if the candidate is a good fit, then increase employer’s chance to get the right freelancer than it was before.</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/ae_private_message/looking-for-viral-content-writer-2/fre-private-message-is-an-extension-of-freelanceengine-with-it-your-employers-can-easily-start-a-private-conversation-with-bidders-before-accepting-the-bid-thus-they-can-understand-if-the-candidat/</link>

	<item>
		<title>Sample Page</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/sample-page/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 25 Aug 2016 09:17:09 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?page_id=2</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

<blockquote>Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>

...or something like this:

<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>

As a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>How It Works</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/how-it-works/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 08:12:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?page_id=1018</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">FreelanceEngine - A Premium Freelance Marketplace WordPress Theme</span></h1>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>FreelanceEngine</strong> is a WordPress theme which helps you to create your own freelance marketplace. Users then can use this site to find their suitable working partners:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Employers can post projects and find the suitable freelancer to work their projects.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Freelancers can find their jobs.</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">In FreelanceEngine, user can act 2 roles as an employer or a freelancer.</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">As an employer, you can easily login to the site and immediately start posting your project. Once your project is displayed, you can search for the suitable freelancer and invite them to bid your project.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">As a freelancer, you can provide your detailed information and find out the potential projects.</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Here’s the main workflow of the FreelanceEngine:</span>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">1. Post a Project</span></h3>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">An employer can be able to post projects after login or signup on the site. </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">There are two kinds of project submission: submit for free or paid to submit a project. </span></li>
</ul>
<h2></h2>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">2. Bid a Project</span></h3>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Freelancers can find different projects on the main page and start bidding to join the interested project by the “</span><b>Apply</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">” button.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Besides, employers can also invite the freelancers first via their profiles as well. After that, the freelancers can take a look at the project details and decide to bid it or not.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2></h2>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">3. Accept a Bid</span></h3>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Employer will review this bid in the project detail page and decide to accept or ignore this bid.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When employer chooses the most suitable freelancer to work his project, he clicks the “</span><b>Accept</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">” button on the bid list.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2></h2>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">4. Open the Workspace</span></h3>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once a bid acceptance, both employer and freelancer can open the workspace to have further discussion regarding the project.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In this page, they can send a private message to each other and offer attached files as well.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2></h2>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">5. Complete the project</span></h3>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Employer will review this project when the freelancer finishes. </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the employer is satisfied with this project, he clicks the “</span><b>Finish</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">” button and writes a review for the freelancer.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">This project is now considered as Completed, the freelancer will press “</span><b>Review &amp; Complete”</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> button to review and rate back for the employer.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If the employer isn’t happy with the freelancer’s performance after reviewing the project, he can hit the “</span><b>Close</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">” button to send a dispute to the admin. </span></li>
</ul>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Trust &amp; Quality</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/trust-quality/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 08:27:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?page_id=1025</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">FreelanceEngine offers you a safe &amp; reliable payment system</span></h1>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">FreelanceEngine payment system is integrated with the Escrow - a helpful feature for the admin to create a trustworthy marketplace. Currently, Escrow is working with PayPal Adaptive, Stripe connection, and Credit to hold money as a neutral third party in the transaction until the service or good is delivered.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Once you enable system, you - the admin of the site will become a contractor between the freelancer and employer. Whenever an employer accepts a bid, he has to send money including budget of that project and commission to the admin. Admin will keep this money until the project is completed.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In case of dispute, admin will play a role as judge to make the final decision to refund money to the employer or send the payment for the freelancer based on their reasons. Hence, FreelanceEngine can give you the ability to ensure the safety of each transaction and the benefits of your users. </span>[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Let’s look at this example for better understanding the flow:
<h3><span style="color: #ec6367;">Employer accepts a bid</span></h3>
When the employer accepts a bid, he has to transfer money including budget &amp; commission fee through a payment gateway (PayPal Adaptive or Stripe Connection) or Credit. Admin will keep part of the payment during the project is in progress. Once the project is completed, money held in Escrow is manually transferred to the freelancer. In case your site uses Credit, money is transferred to the available balance column of the freelancer.
<h2></h2>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h3><span style="color: #ec6367;">Freelancer withdraws (in case </span><span style="color: #ec6367;">Escrow Credit is used in your site)</span></h3>
If you use Escrow Credit as a payment method in your site, freelancer has to send a withdrawal request to the admin to get cash. The admin reviews the request and send the payment to that freelancer.
<h2></h2>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h3><span style="color: #ec6367;">Manage the dispute</span></h3>
Sometimes, the admin has to involve in a debate. It occurs when the employer isn’t satisfied with freelancer’s performance; or the freelancer doesn’t complete a project on time or deliver the work deliver the work with bad quality. In contract, freelancer believes he has done this project well but the employer doesn’t mark this project as “Finish”, the freelancer can also send a dispute request to admin. Beside, dispute also may arise during the project, freelancer discontinues or employer closes in the middle of the project. Of course, either of them have to explain reasons behind the action.

At that moment, admin will play a role as judge to make the final decision to refund money to the employer or send the payment for the freelancer based on their reasons.

Besides providing a payment system which helps all transactions work smoothly and safely, FreelanceEngine also offers admins many monetizing methods:

<b>By Commission</b>: You can monetize by charging commission on each transaction made in your marketplace.

<b>By Submit Listing Plans</b>: You can charge your employer for posting a project.

<b>By Bid Plans</b>: You can charge your freelancer for bidding a project.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>About Us</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/about-us/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 08:44:19 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?page_id=1035</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ec6367;"><b>FreelanceEngine</b></span></h1>
<h4 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #808080;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Powerful Project Bidding Theme For Freelance Marketplace</span></i></span></h4>
&nbsp;
<h2><span style="color: #ec6367;">1. Who We Are</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry’s standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It was popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containing Lorem Ipsum passages, and more recently with desktop publishing software like Aldus PageMaker including versions of Lorem Ipsum.</span>
<h2></h2>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h2><span style="color: #ec6367;">2. Why Choose FreelanceEngine</span></h2>
FreelanceEngine helps you:

&nbsp;
<h4>Creative design with Page builder supported</h4>
<ul>
 	<li>Right in the first look, the theme’s header is not just some passive “hero image”. Instead, you can include a background video to put life into your site. Simply leave a trendy &amp; professional impress on your visitors!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
 	<li>For the menu, different from normal menus you usually see, we support a full screen menu giving your users a complete new experience navigating the site. Much more focus!</li>
</ul>
<ul>
 	<li>FreelanceEngine also includes a premium page builder for more customizability. Staying away from complicated processes, you can save tons of time building up your site, right in the front-end. All you need to do is dragging the content blocks to the position you want and order them properly.</li>
</ul>
<h4></h4>
&nbsp;
<h4>Monetize your site right away</h4>
<ul>
 	<li>With FreelanceEngine, you can create different payment plans charging employers to post their projects as well as featuring them. Using this way, you can generate revenue from your freelance marketplace.</li>
 	<li>FreelanceEngine supports the most popular payment gateways such as PayPal, 2CheckOut, and also by manual bank transfer, making it easier for your users to complete transactions and for you to collect your earnings.</li>
</ul>
<h4></h4>
&nbsp;
<h4>Optimize on-site user experience</h4>
<ul>
 	<li>We help you experience simplicity creating the site and make sure you can also share this experience for those who are using your site.</li>
 	<li>For the employers, we offer “Post a project” option with tons of great options such as project title, budget, needed skills, category and description. They can specify all qualities they expect from the freelancers.</li>
 	<li>For the freelancers, they can access to the member areas to build up their professional profiles. All needed details are offered. They can insert their personal information, their hourly rate as well as adding their portfolios.</li>
 	<li>Users can use the focus search to find their suitable partners. Simply insert the keyword and the system will give all detailed results including project title, posted date, budge, etc.</li>
</ul>
<h2></h2>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h2><span style="color: #ec6367;">3. How It Works</span></h2>
<h4>Find suitable participants for the projects</h4>
Employer posts a project and freelancers bid this project. Then, employer choose the most suitable freelancer to work the project by accepting a bid.
<h4>Enter workspace</h4>
After a bid acceptance, both employer &amp; freelancer open workspace for further discussion regarding the project.
<h4>Review</h4>
Employer will review this project when the freelancer finishes. If the employer is satisfied with this project, he clicks the Finish button and writes a review for the freelancer. If not, he can send a dispute to the admin
<h2></h2>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h2><span style="color: #ec6367;">4. Meet Our Team</span></h2>

	<item>
		<title>Privacy Policy</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/privacy-policy/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 08:52:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?page_id=1038</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">EngineThemes Privacy Policy</span></h1>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">This privacy policy discloses the privacy practices for EngineThemes. This privacy policy applies solely to information collected by this website. It will notify you of the following:</span>

&nbsp;
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">What personally identifiable information is collected from you through the website, how it is used and with whom it may be shared.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">What choices are available to you regarding the use of your data.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The security procedures in place to protect the misuse of your information.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">How you can correct any inaccuracies in the information.</span></li>
</ul>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">1. Information Collection, Use, and Sharing</span></h2>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We are the sole owners of the information collected on this site. We only have access to/collect information that you voluntarily give us via email or other direct contacts from you. We will not sell or rent this information to anyone.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We will use your information to respond to you, regarding the reason you contacted us. We will not share your information with any third party outside of our organization, other than as necessary to fulfill your request, e.g. to ship an order.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Unless you ask us not to, we may contact you via email in the future to tell you about specials, new products or services, or changes to this privacy policy.</span>[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">2. Your Access to and Control Over Information</span></h2>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">You may opt out of any future contacts from us at any time. You can do the following at any time by contacting us via the email address or phone number on our website:</span>

&nbsp;
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">See what data we have about you, if any.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Change/correct any data we have about you.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Have us delete any data we have about you.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Express any concern you have about our use of your data.</span></li>
</ul>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h2><span style="color: #ec6367;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">3. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Security</span></span></h2>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We take precautions to protect your information. When you submit sensitive information via the website, your information is protected both online and offline.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Wherever we collect sensitive information (such as credit card data), that information is encrypted and transmitted to us in a secure way. You can verify this by looking for a closed lock icon at the bottom of your web browser, or looking for “https” at the beginning of the address of the web page.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">While we use encryption to protect sensitive information transmitted online, we also protect your information offline. Only employees who need the information to perform a specific job (for example, billing or customer service) are granted access to personally identifiable information. The computers/servers in which we store personally identifiable information are kept in a secure environment.</span>[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400; color: #ec6367;">4. Updates</span></h2>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Our Privacy Policy may change from time to time and all updates will be posted on this page.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you feel that we are not abiding by this privacy policy, you should contact us immediately via <a href="mailto:support@enginethemes.com" target="_blank">support@enginethemes.com</a>.</span>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Write a Technical Report</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/write-a-technical-report/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Sep 2016 06:39:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[nikolaospachis]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=771</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The project will consist of writing a Software test plan development, implementation and documenting the use of effective exception handling.</p>
<p>The project will be rewarded to a person who displays a very good command of English, both in writing and grammar. It will be also rewarded to a person with a vast background of software testing and writing. </p>
<p>Attached you will find a document which contains an overview of what the program does.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Translate Content from English to Spanish (South America)</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/translate-content-from-english-to-spanish-south-america/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 05 Sep 2016 10:55:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[erikanela]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=862</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hello,</p>
<p>I would need your help to translate a list of words/sentences from english to spanish (Argentina spanish preferred). These words/sentences are used throughout our website/platform and can be found in the attached php file.</p>
<p>Here are some detailed instructions:</p>
<p>1 - Please download Sublime Text 2 (Text Editor)</p>
<p>2 - Open the attached .php file in Sublime Text 2</p>
<p>3 - Update the translation to Spanish in that same .php file.</p>
<p>The spanish translation should be on the right side.</p>
<p>For example, </p>
<p>  "Edit My Subscription" =&gt; "Edit My Subscription",</p>
<p>could become:</p>
<p>  "Edit My Subscription" =&gt; "Cambiar mi suscripción"</p>
<p>(this is probably not a good translation, came from Google Translate :))</p>
<p>4 - Note that some content might already be translated in Spanish, you can either keep it or translate it if you think there is a better translation</p>
<p>5 - Note that the text will be showing up on the web/on a platform so the translation should be as short as possible. If you have the option between 2 words as a translation, try to keep the shortest version.</p>
<p>5 - IMPORTANT</p>
<p>Make sure you save the file with UTF-8 Encoding. Sublime Text 2 will allow you to save with encoding. Here is how to do it on a Mac:</p>
<p>Go to following menu: File &gt; Save with Encoding &gt; UTF-8</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We are looking for 2-3 unique blogs and articles to be written each week. Based around the topic of Digital Marketing.</p>
<p>Topics can be varied such as lead generation, funnels, creating content etc</p>

<p>Our market are small &amp; medium business owners who we can educate about digital marketing.</p>
<p>The blogs will be created to bring people into our business.</p>
<p>Our end product is providing digital services such as webiste builds, copywriting, sales funnels, design work etc</p>
<p>Thanks</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/web-application-dashboard-testing-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 07:41:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[dorisclarke]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=978</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We are looking for competent and quick testers to go through a Dashboard based system in a multi-platform and multi-browser fashion.</p>
<p>We need our web application to be thoroughly tested in 10 days. The project will be awarded on Monday the 8th of August. The project will need to be completed by Friday 19th of August.</p>
<p>The testing will require you to test the quiz in:</p>
<p>- Google Chrome.</p>
<p>- FireFox.</p>
<p>- Internet Explorer.</p>
<p>- Safari.</p>
<p>All tests will need to be run on a desktop/laptop device, an Android Tablet, and an iPad.</p>
<p>You will be required to report any issues, bugs, or suggested fixes by referencing the specific question as logged in the console. A screenshot of all issues, bugs or suggested fixes is required.</p>
<p>You will be required to test each section of the web application.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Why It is Important to Choose The Right Business Model for Your Freelancing Bidding Site</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/why-it-is-important-to-choose-the-right-business-model-for-your-freelancing-bidding-site/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 08 Sep 2016 07:25:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?p=1330</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8500" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/09/freelancing-business-model.jpg" alt="freelancing business model" width="768" height="400" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">“Make money online” as a freelancer has increasingly been a popular choice among young people. To build a platform connecting freelancers and clients, hence, has great potential to grow. If you plan to start your business career following this path, one of the first things to take into consideration is the proper business model you will use for your business.  </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For an online freelance site, which business models that are available and how each differs from the others? Generally speaking, business model is the strategy on what you will do with your site to generate revenue. A good business idea together with an appropriate business model promises to be an effective monetization tool.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">This post will list out possible business models to help you pick up one that works best on your site.</span><!--more-->
<h2>1. Project listings</h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8506" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/09/project-listings.png" alt="freelancing business model - project listings" width="398" height="397" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">On a freelance bidding site, your main contents come from projects posted by clients. You can monetize this action by making clients pay to have projects listed. One way to do this is offering various packages, each of which allows for a number of projects posted and includes other add-ons. Paying by packages also reduces the hassle of payment made each time clients post a new project.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Collecting fee per project listing is necessary as it helps ensure content quality. People won’t spend money on posting untrue projects that have no value to them. On the other hand, this is a potential monetization method as you’re able to capture a portion of all listings on site.</span>
<h2>2. Bidding fees</h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8502" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/09/auction.png" alt="freelancing business model - bidding fees" width="768" height="401" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Project bidding is a typical feature of freelancing sites. It allows freelancers to bid for projects they have interest in while increases the chance for clients to find the best partner to complete the projects.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Similarly to project listings, bidding packages are given for freelancers to choose. Each bidding plan has a specified number of available bids and other optional offerings.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In a freelancing website where bidding is a key function, asking freelancers to pay for each bid is necessary. Why? Let’s compare paid bid and free bid. Mentioning the former, each bid costs freelancers money which makes them consider carefully before bidding on any project. This makes each bid a real one, ensures the quality of the bidding. On the contrary, “free to bid” alternative makes it so much easier for freelancers to bid on any project. There might be cases when freelancers bid and get accepted by clients but then quit, which is such a waste of time for clients. Unhappy clients are the situation you never want to deal with.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As a result, if you integrate bidding fee model into your business strategy, try to come up with a reasonable fee per bid, not too high but also not too low.   </span>
<h2>3. Membership fees</h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8505" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/09/membership-fees.png" alt="freelancing business model - membership fees" width="401" height="401" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Membership fee is a user-based business model in which users have to pay a fee to become a client or freelancer on your platform.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The willingness to pay before getting any value from your site shows that users have serious intention of joining. Serious members possibly mean better quality and more popular reputation for your website. Specifically, clients have many valuable projects to list and freelancers are more skillful and professional.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">However, good points also come with challenges. To persuade users to join, you need to be able to prove that the benefits from working on your site far outweigh the cost. Freelancers would want to see the opportunity to work on thousands-of-dollar projects whereas clients prefer to employ the best freelancers who can excellently carry out all project’ requirements.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In fact, as the nature of projects listed on freelancing bidding websites is quite complex, applying membership fee model on your site is a viable option.</span>
<h2>4. Featured projects</h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8504" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/09/featured-projects.png" alt="freelancing business model - featured projects" width="398" height="398" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">When your website reaches to the level of hundreds or even thousands of new projects posted everyday, it is quite difficult for a project to stand out from the crowd. It is when featured project comes in hand as a savior to draw more attention from potential freelancers.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">However, alone featured project is not strong enough to be your main model. First, not all users have the urgent need of showing their projects on top of page. Second, this model might not prove powerful during the first days of site establishment when project listings are not plenty. Therefore, if you want to make this feature available, use it as a component of the main model.   </span>
<h2>5. Advertising</h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8501" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/09/advertising.png" alt="freelancing business model - advertising" width="768" height="401" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">This is definitely a classic form of making money online. Browsing through the Internet, you have surely seen banner ads, pop-ups, video ads, etc. appear somewhere on any websites trying to grab your attention. That is how this model works to reach Internet users. When your website has attracted a high enough amount of daily traffic, advertisers will come to you to have their ads put on your site.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Onsite advertising has long been a popular money making technique but it is getting tougher than ever since most users don’t like ads. Many apps have been used to block ads as users find ads annoying and irritating.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">This business model is frequently employed on content platforms where users crave for information. However, on a freelance bidding site, users don’t expect to see ads. Too many ads can lead to unhappy customers, which in turn reduces site traffic. So consider this model carefully.</span>
<h2>6. Commission fees</h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8503" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/09/commission-new.png" alt="freelancing business model - commission fees" width="398" height="396" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Freelancing bidding website is a two-sided marketplace whose value is created by the exchange between clients and freelancers. The ultimate result of this exchange is that clients get their projects done while freelancers earn money by providing skills to complete the tasks. To monetize from this exchange, commission fee is the widely used business model. You will charge a percentage or decent amount per transaction initiated inside the platform.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Why is commission fee the most popular model on the 2-sided platform? This is because it is triggered from the very core value, which is the transaction between clients and freelancers, your site provides for users. And this core value is the biggest reason customers need your platform. To get what they need, your customers are willing to pay for it. As long as you charge a reasonable commission rate, this business model is an assurance for long-term sustainability.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The second advantage of commission model is that you won’t miss out any transactions on your platform. The revenue, therefore, is higher than that of other models.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The challenge part of this model lies in its pricing level and structure: how much you should charge and how to distribute the burden between clients and freelancers. To come up with the final rate requires intensive research and depends on your business. Upwork has recently posed an example on this issue. In the past, the rate charged for clients and freelancers was 0% and 10% respectively. Now the game has changed. As the page explained that to reduce the burden maintaining the service, clients are required to pay 2.75% more over the top of each payment as processing fee, while the rate for freelancers varies from 5% to 20% depending on the project value.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We can’t say whether it is a proper change but this instance shows that to choose the right things to do is hard but it is even harder to do things right. This is also what I would like to say before ending this post. Building a business is a long run goal requiring great passion and hard work. But every problem has a solution. Choose the right business model for your freelancing website and apply it in the most effective way to achieve success.</span>

<em>Images by Freepik.</em>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>How to Build a Freelance Bidding Website with WordPress</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/how-to-build-a-freelance-bidding-website-with-wordpress/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 09 Sep 2016 03:47:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?p=1473</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8405" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/08/featured-image-1.jpg" alt="How to Build a Freelance Bidding Website with WordPress" width="768" height="400" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Freelancing websites play a perfect role in connecting clients in need of getting projects done and freelancers, from all over the world, who are willing to provide services and get paid. For two sides to come together, freelancers can bid for any potential projects and clients will pick the most suitable one for their projects.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Having the intention of building a freelancing site, you must be wondering what steps you should take to realize your idea and bring it online. This is also the topic I’ll be covering shortly. But before that, I will talk about freelance marketplace concept as well as niche markets for your business.</span><!--more-->
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bid-based freelance marketplace</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Freelance websites like Guru, Elance, and Upwork use reverse bidding as the operating concept for their marketplace. What is it?</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Let’s first mention ordinary bidding (auction) in which buyers will compete by offering high price to get a good or service. The buyer paying the highest price wins. In reverse bidding, seller and buyer roles are interchanged. Sellers are the bidders. Buyers will consider among different bids and decide which to pick. The chosen seller doesn’t need to be the one offering the lowest price.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Similarly, in a freelance site, when a client posts a project, multiple freelancers will bid for that project. Client will then pick up the freelancer he thinks is the most suitable.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">How this concept works on a freelance site?</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-8408" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/08/freelance.png" alt="How to Build a Freelance Bidding Website with WordPress 2" width="550" height="550" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In the first place, a client will sign up on your site and post a project with detailed description, requirements, estimated budget and time.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Then, freelancers on site browse through the page and find this project. If they are interested, they can bid for the project, offer price and give estimated time of completion. Besides, the client can invite their favorite freelancers to bid for the project.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Client will review each bid offer and have a look at bidders’ profiles (portfolio, working experience, reviews and ratings on site). Based on such evidence, client will choose a suitable bidder and accept the bid. After that, he makes the payment which is held by site admin and will be transferred to freelancer upon project completion.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">During the project, client and freelancer can communicate and exchange information via private chat box on site. Website admin can control the project progress by management tools.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Once the project is finished, freelancers will get paid for their services.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Choose a niche market for your business</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">You may have the question that if the market already has many freelancing sites, why you should join in! Well, while above mentioned successful freelance bidding sites go global covering multiple industries in various regions, you can avoid the severe battle by going small. This is the strategy I think small and medium businesses should consider. The approach could come from two aspects: geography and industry. The former concerns with the range of regions where services are provided, whereas the latter is types of goods and services available on site. Normally, a broader range means more work, larger budgets, and more difficulty.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">With some unique features, it’s not an impossible mission for you to create an outstanding freelance website. It can be a place dedicated to WordPress related stuffs only where people post projects about WordPress and freelancers with proficient WordPress skills will offer services on your site. Moreover, you can build a bidding site for users in your city only. Local people posts their requirements and freelancers living nearby who find these projects interesting will bid for them.   </span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Think of must-have functions for your freelance bidding site</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8407" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/08/freelance.jpg" alt="How to Build a Freelance Bidding Website with WordPress 3" width="768" height="401" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To make your bidding site seem as what it is, build its skeleton in which the most basic and important elements are considered in the first place. For instance, you implement several functions on site but leave bidding function for later. It’s not the way you do it as your site cannot be seen as a bidding site without its typical feature. Below is a list of some necessary functions in a freelance bidding website.</span>
<ul>
 	<li><b>Signup  &amp; User Profile</b></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Projects on your site can be viewed by visitors. However, to do certain tasks, visitors are required to sign up and become a member. Only logged-in users can view private contents, submit projects (client role), bid for projects (freelancer role), make payments, contact with clients or freelancers.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">User profiles for two roles should have two distinct design as freelancers might have other things to showcase. In a freelancer profile, fields needed include self description, experience, category, skills, portfolio, reviews and ratings. In profile space of clients, there’s no portfolio, category or skills. Instead, clients will need the ability to manage his projects. Specifically, submitted projects are listed with details about budget, working freelancer, date and time, service delivery. Also, clients can edit, pause, archive or delete any project. Moreover, he can post a project from here  and control bidding offers from freelancers.</span>
<ul>
 	<li><b>Project Submission</b></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">This is of course a must have function on a freelance site. Clients needing jobs done will submit a project with job title, detailed description, estimated budget, required skills, project category, any attachment, etc. Next, site admin will review the project content and approve for the project to be published on site. From this time, freelancers can browse for projects and apply.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To make money from this function, you can ask clients to buy a package with which they can post 15 projects in a specified period of time.</span>
<ul>
 	<li><b>Project Bidding</b></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">This is the reverse bidding concept mentioned at the beginning. With every project posted, clients hope to employ the best freelancer to do the job. The bidding function helps clients attract potential freelancers. A bidding form is expected to have project detailed offer in which freelancers outline their plan to execute the project, price, project duration and attachment.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For admin, to monetize from this function, freelancers will have to pay for each bid made. Freelancers can buy a package allowing for 10 bids for example.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Clients can invite specific freelancers to bid for the projects to increase the rate of choosing the best freelancer.</span>
<ul>
 	<li><b>Private Message</b></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Effective communication is the key to success. A private chat space will boost the interaction between client and freelancer, clear any job requirements to produce the best outcome. Every time a new conversation is initiated, a notification email is sent to the receiver. Users can send text message, attach any necessary files from this.</span>
<ul>
 	<li><b>Project Management</b></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Now that the project is started, freelancer will embark on the task. During this period, you should provide both parties - client and freelancer - a tool to track the progress and manage the overall project.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Milestone is used to break the project into smaller stages. Each milestone has a deadline and different statuses. Upon completing a single milestone, freelancer will deliver the result and change that milestone’s status to Completed for example. Client will review and change the milestone status accordingly. If he is satisfied with the delivery, it is changed to Finished and freelancer will move onto other milestones. Otherwise, client will reopen the milestone and freelancer has to work more on it.  </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In case conflict happens, both parties have the right to send a dispute to you. You are the judge to decide who wins and gets the money. To make this decision, you can access to all information and material exchanged between the two on your platform, such as message, any files, milestone, etc.</span>
<ul>
 	<li><b>Project Payment</b></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Provide popular payment gateways like PayPal, Stripe, 2Checkout or the ones frequently used in your local.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In this freelance model, after client makes payment for a project, the money is not directly transferred to freelancer to avoid the situation in which freelancer might get away without completing the task or not do his best for the project. Therefore, the payment from client is withheld by you - the third party between client and freelancer. Escrow system is a good solution. Once the project is finished, money is automatically released to freelancer.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Technically prepare for these things</span></h2>
<ul>
 	<li><b>Domain:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Get for your site a name. You can read some tips </span><a href="https://www.enginethemes.com/choose-good-website-domain-name/" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">here</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> on how to choose a good domain name.</span></li>
 	<li><b>Hosting provider: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">After domain, hosting service is what you need for online presence. Choosing a good provider to host your website helps avoid server downtime and ensure fast loading time.  </span></li>
 	<li><b>WordPress: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is by far the most popular content management system. Unless you aim to build a global business with tens of thousands of customers per day, </span><a href="https://wordpress.org/" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">WordPress</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is an effective platform for you to get started.</span></li>
 	<li><b>Premium Freelance Theme: <span style="font-weight: 400;">Currently, there are some freelance bidding WordPress themes available on the market. Do a research and explore pros as well as cons of each theme to choose a suitable theme for your needs.</span></b></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Take a look at FreelanceEngine Theme</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8406" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/08/FRE.png" alt="How to Build a Freelance Bidding Website with WordPress 4" width="768" height="356" />

<a href="https://www.enginethemes.com/themes/freelanceengine/" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">FreelanceEngine</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is a powerful WordPress bidding theme for freelance marketplace. Main benefits include:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Powerful Income Tool: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">There are multiple ways to make profits from your freelance marketplace website. You can charge fees for posting jobs, featuring jobs with ads included, and take commission fees of each project via Escrow system.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Safe, easy project bidding and transaction: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">With Escrow system, freelancers can effortlessly bid for favorite tasks while clients can invite specific freelancers to bid, and everyone can be secure in the knowledge that all the money is safe with this system.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Highly customizable without coding knowledge: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">FreelanceEngine Team dives deep to produce the best and highly customizable theme for you and ensure a smooth user flow. Build any layout you can imagine with intuitive drag and drop editor – no programming knowledge required.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>More exciting features:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Besides, FreelanceEngine has tons of supportive features to help you build a great freelancing bidding website.</span></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://www.enginethemes.com/themes/freelanceengine/" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">View its features</span></a>

<a href="https://www.enginethemes.com/themes/freelanceengine/" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">View live demo</span></a>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Final thoughts</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Writing this post, I hope to provide you an overview of general steps to build a freelance bidding website for your business. It is to understand how the bidding concept works on freelance platform, then determine your niche market, dig into major functions you’re gonna bring on site, find out technical requirements for an online business, and buy a premium freelance WordPress theme working along well with your strategy.</span>

<em>Featured image by Freepik.</em>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Key Features of a Freelance Website (Part 1)</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/key-features-of-a-freelance-website-part-1/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 09 Sep 2016 03:48:29 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?p=1476</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8317" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/feature-image.jpg" alt="key features in a freelance website" width="768" height="401" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Outsourcing service has become popular thanks to multiple benefits it brings to business. It is especially the case for small and medium businesses since you can’t do all the jobs by yourself. Freelancing websites have raised as a platform connecting project owners and skillful freelancers.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re planning to develop a freelancing website offering this kind of service but haven’t determined yet what features are needed, take a look at this article. There are 2 parts in this series; in part 1 I will go over core features to get your site up and running, then part 2 will introduce other additional features to help you build an advanced freelance website.   </span><!--more-->
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">What are the key features in a Freelance Website?</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Key features in a freelance website are the most basic ones to make your site considered a freelance platform. Take some time to put yourself in freelancer’s or project owner’s shoes and think about their expectation of a freelance website. For example, freelancers would want to have  profiles to advertize themselves, while employers expect a project submission form in the front-end. And both would love to have project bidding function so that freelancers can bid for projects they love and employers can invite their favorite freelancers to bid. Considering the business side, a freelance website has to integrate monetization plans together with multiple payment gateways. Also, easy customization, responsive design, and SEO friendly are important features you should consider.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Project submission</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8320" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/project-submission.png" alt="freelance website feature - project submission" width="565" height="531" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To trigger project owners to submit their projects, a submission form should be well designed and available in the front-end. In the form, employers should be able to input project name, the category it belongs to, its budget, project description, and spaces to attach any necessary files.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Freelancer profile</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8319" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/freelancer-profile.png" alt="freelance website feature - freelancer profile" width="1156" height="491" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In an online world where anyone can go anonymous, a profile with basic information about a person is preferred. Likewise, in a freelance website, a public profile for freelancers is a must-have feature to help project owners have the very first image about the freelancer they will work with. On the other hand, a vivid profile is a strong supporting tool to help freelancers with personal branding. So, what to expect in a profile? Besides information about name, nationality, skills, self description, freelancers should be able to upload their portfolio which is the most convincing evidence to showcase their professional expertise.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Project bidding</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8318" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/bidding.png" alt="freelance website feature - project bidding" width="581" height="514" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">This is surely one of the most desired feature in a freelance website. Unlike micro services, projects are bigger in scale, outsourcing fee is higher, so employers need to consider and choose which freelancer to assign the task to. To do this, it is recommended that each project have the Bid button to let many freelancers bid for it. After that, project owner will choose the most appropriate candidate for the job. Moreover, project owners could also invite their favorite freelancers to bid for the projects.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To help employers choose a good freelancer, reverse bid is applied where multiple freelancers will bid for a project and employers will pick the most suitable one. Any freelancers can bid for the project and could know the bid values of each other. Employers will rely not only on bid price to choose a freelancer but also on other factors like freelancer portfolio, experience and skills.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Monetization plan</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Revenue generating methods are a vital part of every business. In a freelance website connecting project owners and freelancers, which plans can you use to earn money from your users? When looking for a freelance WordPress theme, check if multiple monetization packages are supported. There are several ways to charge your users, such as collecting commission fee per project on your website, charging freelancers for every bid they make, and making project owners to pay when they want to list their projects on your site.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Have a thorough research of the business model you will pursue and then pick up the theme that offers monetization plans that meet your strategy.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Different payment gateways</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Flexibility in payment gateways help trigger your users to take on more transactions. Popular gateways like PayPal, 2Checkout or Stripe have wide coverage over many countries in different continents, which create utmost convenience for more users to join your platform. In case the majority of your users reside in locals where these payment gateways are not available yet, local methods should be integrated into your payment system.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fully responsive</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8321" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/Responsive-design.jpg" alt="freelance website feature - responsive design" width="1024" height="417" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Responsive design is the current trend and it is certain that your site will lose many traffic if it fails to meet this expectation. People are going mobile more and more these days, making it extremely important to have a fully responsive site which runs seamlessly on every device not only desktop but also mobile phone, tablet, etc. Having all elements on your site run fast and are adaptable on any screen size is truly an advantage.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Intuitive page builder</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">For a businessman who hardly has any coding skill and is on tight budget, drag &amp; drop feature to customize the website is a great solution.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Check if any page builder tool (Visual Composer for example) is comes together with the theme, a front-end customizer is even greater. With this advantage, you can easily create, drag &amp; drop blocks and widgets to the positions you want to put them in page. This feature efficiently saves your time and effort since it requires no specific coding knowledge.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">SEO friendly</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8322" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/seo-friendly-image.jpg" alt="freelance website feature - SEO friendly" width="800" height="600" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Last but not least, an issue that every business cares about is how to bring more traffic to site. The last core feature has something to do with this which is being SEO friendly. A theme that is built with SEO friendly structure could significantly support your site in increasing rank in search results. Schema structure helps define your contents to communicate with search engines and social networks.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">FreelanceEngine theme is developed with all these features in mind to deliver a premium freelance platform for your business.</span>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">[button type="view" link="https://www.enginethemes.com/themes/freelanceengine/"]Check it out[/button]</span></p>

<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Final thoughts</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Writing this post, I hope to help you determine important features for your freelance website. To choose a theme that is appropriate and meets all demands of your business model can be a daunting task. At first stage, try not to be amazed by tons of supplementary features but to focus on these core functionalities. Once your site is setup with these fundamental functions, add other cool stuffs later. The next part of this series will list out some additional features for a competitive freelance website.</span>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Key Features of a Freelance Website (Part 2)</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/key-features-of-a-freelance-website-part-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 09 Sep 2016 03:49:23 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?p=1478</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8352" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/08/featured-image.jpg" alt="key features in a freelance website" width="768" height="404" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In the </span><a href="https://www.enginethemes.com/key-features-freelance-website-part-1/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">previous post</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, I went over core important features that should be cared for in the first stages of building your freelancing website. After getting your site up and running with such key functions, it’s time you considered furnituring your site with supplementary features to attract more users. So this post is about additional features needed for a freelance website.</span><!--more-->
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Advanced Search</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">This is a basic function installed in almost online sites. Both project owners and freelancers need Search bar to quickly find their needs. They can search by keyword, filter by category or sort by different criteria, etc.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Project Workspace</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Having this function will increase working effectiveness between project owner and freelancer. The workspace is where the two will exchange messages, deliver the results, and manage the project progress by status.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">With this feature, project owner and freelancer can work and communicate right on your platform and there’s no need to rely on other third party.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Review &amp; Rating</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">A drawback of working online is that we don’t know the people we work with in person. Feedback system comes in as a reliable source for us to refer to. In a freelancing website, you need this feature available for both freelancers and project owners.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For project owners, reviews and ratings from freelancers they worked with might help other freelancers know their working styles, their attitudes and requirements. On the other hand, receiving positive feedbacks from many project owners is potential for freelancers in getting more invitation to bid in the future. To ensure the reliability of such feedbacks, make it only available for both parties to write review for the other when they finished a project.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dispute Management</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sometimes things don’t go in the way you want they to. Not all projects are completed successfully. There might be some reasons here and there causing freelancers to want to stop doing the projects or making project owners demand cancelling the job. So, in this case, you need to intervene in as a referee. Should anything unwanted happen during the project, project owner or freelancer is able to file a dispute to you. As a neutral third party, you will consider all the evidence provided to decide who wins and receives the money.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">User Dashboard</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Each user needs a private dashboard to manage his information on site. In this place, users can edit details of their profile, account, manage all projects, bids and messages.</span>

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8354" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/08/user-dashboard.png" alt="freelance website - user dashboard" width="768" height="467" />
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Notification System</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Users are not online 24/24 so they need notifications to tell them what happened while they were away. You can setup a notification bar on the website and also email templates to notify users important events like new project, bid invitation, dispute result, etc.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Customize Bar</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">A quick customize bar in front-end will help you conveniently change style and appearance of key elements on site, for example, header and footer color, body color, heading font, content font size.</span>

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8353" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/08/color-style-picker.png" alt="freelance website - customize bar" width="375" height="515" />
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Custom Sidebar</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Besides main content layout, sidebars are where you can flexibly arrange contents you want to show to users as a quick reference. WordPress themes can offer you with built-in widgets so that you can easily drag and drop any widgets to an appropriate sidebar.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Translation Support</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Usually, if not all, themes are displayed in English language. So translation is requested for websites writing in other languages. All contents on site will be listed in a section for you to translate theme into your own language.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">After a new theme version is released, there might be some texts added to site. A good theme will make the latest update of these additional contents in the list so that you can make an instant translation for your website.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Plugin compatibility</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">A premium WordPress theme could already integrate some popular plugins to make it even more advanced for your usage. That said, there may be many other plugins you want to install in the future. It is good to discover if the theme you’re testing is well compatible to many different popular plugins.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Check Out FreelanceEngine Theme</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">FreelanceEngine is a premium WordPress theme making it easier than ever for you to build a freelancing website. It is highly customizable with intuitive drag and drop page builder and is equipped with many features to meet your business strategy.</span>
<p style="text-align: center;">[button type="buy" class="btn-shake" link="https://www.enginethemes.com/themes/freelanceengine/"]Find Out[/button]</p>
