	<item>
		<title>10 Tips to Improve Your Website’s Conversion Rates</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/10-tips-to-improve-your-websites-conversion-rates/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 09 Sep 2016 03:50:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?p=1480</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8302" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/conversion-rate.png" alt="improve conversion rates" width="768" height="401" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Having a high conversion rate is what all businesses want for their websites. It also means the website is effectively designed in the way that attracts a great number of visitors to take the desired action, which, for most eCommerce sites, is to buy a product or service. As a result, the more visitors are converted into customers, the more revenue for your business.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">While marketing strategies, such as SEO, Google ads, social marketing, try to drive more traffic to your website, conversion optimization plans play an important role in turning your site visitors into customers.</span><!--more-->

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To improve conversion rate on your website requires thorough research about user behavior when visitors explore your website. That said, there are tactics that encourage more and more visitors to become your loyal customers. This article will outline 10 tips you can carry out to optimize conversion rate.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">1. A/B testing</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8307" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/split-testing.jpg" alt="conversion rates - A/B testing" width="768" height="401" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A/B testing (split testing) is the method that you create different versions of your page with some tweaks and test to see which works better with higher conversion rates. Due to the fact that your audience is unique, what you think works well might turn to be a bad choice when it comes to your audience. Therefore, the best way to figure out what works well and what needs further improvement is to do A/B testing.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">To split testing, you can use </span><a href="https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1745152?hl=en"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Google Content Experiments</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of Google Analytics which is a free and easy to use tool.</span>

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8306" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/split-testing-in-Google-Analytics.jpg" alt="conversion rates - A/B testing" width="600" height="561" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">First, set up your goal and the percentage of traffic you want to send to experiment. Then input the destination URLs of the original page you want to test and of other variations. You will be given an experiment code to add to your original page. When all is setup, you’re ready to run start the testing and see which is performing better.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">2. Create urgency for immediate action</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Urgency notifications like “There’re only 3 items left” or “The last day to get the discount” have proved to be effective in urging people to buy right away. When there’s a specific deadline or scarcity for special offers, people will tend not to delay but take the buying process immediately for they don’t want to miss out the chance.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">However, be careful to choose a proper type of urgency depending on your products or services. For example, if you offer digital products which never run out of stock, using the statement saying something like “5 items left in stock” is not gonna work and can cause reverse effect to your business.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">3. Show the benefits</span></h2>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8303" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/benefits.png" alt="conversion rates - show the benefits" width="799" height="329" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A landing page that sells has not only good design but also excellent contents. Contents are what your customers will read and are your opportunity to persuade people why they should choose your products over the ones from other competitors. So, what are the key takeaways to create great contents for your website? Here are some:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Show value proposition:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> What is value proposition? It is a statement of value you will give your customers. It convinces users how your products better solve and improve customers’ problems than similar offerings. Having a specific value proposition will help differentiate your company from other competitors, show your uniqueness and strengths. Also, visitors will find it easier to understand your company, your products, and to determine how your offerings will help them improve the situations.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Great copy to make it easy to read:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Once you have set up your value proposition, deliver it in a way that all visitors can read it and understand easily. This is very important as they are your potential customers and the target you want to communicate with. If your messages are written in terminological terms that only economy majored people can understand, you have failed in delivering your values to a lot of potential customers.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>More benefits, fewer features:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Most importantly, people buy why you do it, not what you do it. This is consistent with the value proposition focus. Your customers are more interested in the benefits your products offer than the features. Let’s say one of your item has 20 features, many of which are similar to other products in the market but some of which are different. These don’t make much sense until you take advantage of the unique features to talk about the benefits your customers will get using your product with such advancing functionalities.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">4. Use Call To Action</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Each page on your website should be designed to serve a specific purpose and navigate users towards a desired action. In such situation, the presence of Call To Action (CTA) is to finalize the our navigation. CTA can be in the form of a link or a button, however; the latter is preferred and easier to draw the attention of readers. How to create good copy for these CTA buttons that optimize the click through rate and where to put them in a page are the concerns to provoke an immediate response from users.  </span>

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8305" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/CTA.png" alt="conversion rates - call to action" width="629" height="220" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A CTA is usually an action verb that creates a sense of urgency like “Shop Now”, “Buy Today” or “Learn More”. The length of text should be short.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Moreover, pay attention to CTA colors of button and text. Each color has a unique meaning and evoke different feelings, and also choose the color that is in harmony with other elements in the page. CTA text should be a bit bigger than other text in the page to capture attention. In order to make your CTA button catch the eye, create a sufficient space around it to make it outstanding from the rest.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">5. Offer proof</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">People won’t trust whatever you claim on your website if it seems unreliable. Therefore, information posted on your site should be backed up with sources.</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Testimonials: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Customer reviews and ratings for your products should come from real customers and about the real experience they had. Internet users are clever and they can realize if such testimonials are real or just made up by your content team.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Social proof: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is a great way to show visitors how many customers have bought and used your products. The more customers you have, the easier it might be to persuade potential customers to buy products from your company.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><b>Case studies:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Real experience shared by other customers is the best evidence to show how your products benefit customers with their business.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">6. Create relationship with customers</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">For many visitors, they don’t buy your products the first time they visit your site. Asking visitors for the purchase too fast might cause you to lose many sales. Especially, for high value products that request a thorough research process, you need to give your customers more time to make the final decision. To turn these visitors into your customers, it’s a need to establish a good engagement with them, make them commit and trust your brand.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">For digital products, a demo version or free trial that allows users to try your products before purchase is a good idea to improve conversion. Besides, a blog with helpful articles providing insightful information about the industry and products is another engagement method to build trust of users in your site. Sometimes, sales do not come immediately, but require time and communication effort.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">7. Easy &amp; smooth checkout</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">With the extreme convenience the Internet offers to its users, customers nowadays are becoming less patient. What does this have to do with conversion optimization? When a visitor has picked his favorite items and proceeded to checkout, make it as easy as possible for him to pay for the products.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There are some tips you can use to improve the checkout flow. The first is to have a clear instruction, guiding what customers have to do in each step. As mentioned, people are very easy to give up complicated process. Once customers enter this flow, it’s not recommended that they have to figure out themselves how to purchase from you. The second point is to make users fill in as few fields as possible. In your signup form, instead of asking a lot of different fields, just request important information that you will ever need for further engagement. Signup via Facebook, Twitter, or Google account is another good choice to simplify the process.</span>

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8304" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/checkout1.png" alt="conversion rates - easy checkout" width="425" height="301" />
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">8. Refund guarantee</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">People tend to be more willing to pay for your products if they can return and get the refund in case the products do not meet their expectation or something went wrong. Make sure the refund policy is well communicated so that your site visitors would feel more secure going with your business.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">9. Sell more with Upsell &amp; Cross sell</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Upselling and Cross selling are to encourage your customers to buy more based on the previously purchased items. If done smartly, these methods can increase your revenue. Particularly, when a customer buys an item, your website will recommend related products that the customer might be interested in. Moreover, offering money-saving product packages can motivate people to buy more and as a result, you get more out of an average customer.</span>

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8308" src="https://static.enginethemes.com/2016/07/upsell-amazon.jpg" alt="conversion rates - Upsell" width="768" height="447" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">However, above all, customer experience is what that matters, so make sure these tactics are carried out carefully and are relevant to the items they relate to. Otherwise, customers will find your product recommendation irritating which might negatively affect their purchase.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">10. Visitor retargeting</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">To recapture visitors that almost become your customers is an effective method to optimize conversion rates. According to a research, 68.63% is the average cart abandonment rate of eCommerce stores. To win back a fraction of these visitors is a positive increase in your sales volume. A shopping cart is abandoned when a customer adds some items to the cart but then leave your site before check out selected items.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There might be some reasons for their going away, but it’s clear that they have the purchase intention at that time and you shouldn’t give up on them after only one attempt. In this context, you can set up automation emails sent after a few hours of abandoned cart with a CTA to help them finalize their purchase right away. Another way to recapture almost conversions is ad retargeting. You can use Facebook ads or PPC ads to show the ads of your site to the visitors who had previously came to your website. By viewing these ads, visitors will be reminded of your site and likely to return to finalize the purchase.</span>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Conclusion</span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">These are 10 tips to increase conversion rates. Hope these ideas can help you add more effective measurements to your conversion optimization plan. The tips don’t end here, if you have tried other methods and seen positive effect to your conversion, feel free to add them in the comments.</span>]]></content:encoded>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I need someone to come up with a Facebook marketing strategy for my limited small budget. </p>
<p>Would like someone who has proven experience getting results with low budgets. Ideas or creation of images and copy also required - some already created but want advice on them. </p>
<p>Want someone who can advise how much to test and to help monitor and make suggestions on what to change. </p>
<p>I am a wedding planner and have created an online course for brides who may not want or have the budget for a wedding planner so they can still get the advice to help them plan a beautiful wedding. I have a portion of lesson 1 on budget planning as a lead magnet and my funnel is created with click funnels.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Mathematical</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/mathematical/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 05 Sep 2016 10:21:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[trinebritta]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=833</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify">Dears,</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">It is a very very simple job. We will give you a simple theory of one paragraph. you have to represent it in a mathematical form. It is a long time work. Suitable candidates have been rewarded with regular work. </p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Example:</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Cloud computing is a kind of Internet-based computing that provides shared processing resources and data to computers and other devices on demand. It is a model for enabling ubiquitous, on-demand access to a shared pool of configurable computing resources (e.g., networks, servers, storage, applications and services), which can be rapidly provisioned and released with minimal management effort. Cloud computing and storage solutions provide users and enterprises with various capabilities to store and process their data in third-party data centers. It relies on sharing of resources to achieve coherence and economy of scale, similar to a utility (like the electricity grid) over a network.</p>
<p style="text-align: left"> </p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Orewa - Web Search and add detail to attached Spreadsheet.</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/orewa-web-search-and-add-detail-to-attached-spreadsheet/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 04:10:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[martie]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=873</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi The attached spreadsheet contains 330 businesses, we have the web addresses of 137.</p>
<p>We don't expect all to have web addresses. </p>
<p>Search the web addresses to locate missing web addresses and if located the email address + any additional phone detail offered for each company on the website. </p>
<p>Quality data only, don't make it up, if it is not there, if you are not sure leave it empty. </p>
<p>I would like this data added into the attached spread sheet please.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Remove Objects from Image Using Photoshop</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=926</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kermitlawrence]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=926</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I’m looking for someone to do simple object removal or object addition in an image using Photoshop. You only requires to know basic Photoshop skill, I’ll provide the detailed steps for the task. It will be an advantage if you know quite well in Photoshop. This project is for “Find a Difference Game” between two images.</p>
<p>There are 40 images and each needs to have 5 differences. This is the first project and I’ve similar projects coming up the way.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Find an Accountant</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=997</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[devenwestley]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=997</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We need to make the book keeping, accounting and audit for a limited liability company, for the years 2010 to 2015, all inclusive.</p>
<p>The vouchers are organized in chronological order, and organized well in box files, and numbered consecutively. </p>
<p>We need the usual work done, with NSSF, NHIF, Trial balance, financial statement.</p>
<p>We have bank statements for most of all years in total, we may be missing only a few bank statements for a few months.</p>
<p>We have all cheque sleeves.</p>
<p>A big chunk of the entire book keeping has been done already.</p>
<p>All entries has been done via ETR machine.</p>
<p>Bank reconciliation must be done too, for accuracy purposes.</p>
<p>We do explicitly not need anything to be done on tax. Simply follow tax laws, that is all. </p>
<p>The work will take place at our location.</p>
<p>You will be engaged on usual professional terms and conditions. The bid sum is based on all 6 years, however, we will create a milestone for each year.</p>
<p>We need that you quote (bid) for the total work, which shall include accounting and audit from the point where we provide for you the vouchers, up to the point where we have an annual financial statement.</p>
<p>In terms of accounting method, use the simplest possible method. </p>
<p>IN the period between 2014 and 2016, there has been no activity, therefore, we expect it to be a question about doing a few operations.</p>
<p>Questions are welcome. </p>
<p>If you intend to bid above USD 3,000 for the total work of doing these 6 years, then do not waste your time.</p>
<p>Foreigners should not bid on the task. We need a local from Kenya to bid, as you would need to go through the material.</p>]]></content:encoded>

And find a registration if user are not registered .<br />And I need to also edit my tax percentage (%)<br />My price is $5 for this. Just need auto calculate option.<br />If you want to work with me this is my text project for you. SO THIS I WANT TO BUILD UP A RELATION WITH THIS CONTRACT.</span></p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Create an Animation of 20-30 Video Series</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/create-an-animation-of-20-30-video-series/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 06:53:30 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[aggielorie]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=939</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We, at Classellified, are trying to re-create the online buying and selling experience by building a community where people help each other in their transactions. You can now also bargain online! The novel feature, here, is that the potential buyers also have an option of bidding on the product they wish to buy. Classellified is a one stop place to engage in hassle-free buying and selling. And the amazing part is that you need not worry about getting the best price because we have your back! All you need to do is simply post your advertisement and we will take it forward from there.</p>
<p>Your task will be to build-up a story of at least 20-25 video-series which will help us connect to the audience in the most human-gesture possible. These videos may/may not include the company description above, but they should be engaging enough. We can brainstorm on the content/story. This needs to be get done asap.</p>
<p>Payment will be made on per video-basis. My budget is fixed., ie $30 per video. Only interested people shall bid.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Create RESTful API proxy in .NET</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/create-restful-api-proxy-in-net/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:04:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[pearcedenny]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=945</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I need software created that will act as a proxy between my application and a third-party API service. I would like the proxy to accept the incoming authenticated request, forward it along to the third-party API, wait for the response and then respond back to the application. </p>
<p>The proxy must have the architecture to allow me to modify the response back to the application, whether it is before or after the actual service call. For instance, if I want to add 20 seconds to the API call, the proxy should be able to simulate that. Another example would be to send back a response without ever forwarding it along to the third-party service.</p>
<p>If software like this already exists in .NET in a GitHub project, I will award a finders fee, so please message me. </p>
<p>The first milestone in the project will be to forward a request to a specific third-party API. I will share those details with the winner.</p>
<p>Thanks for reading. Please respond with a non-generic message so I know that you read the entire description.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Drag &#038; Drop M4P Donut Builder</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/drag-drop-m4p-donut-builder/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 07:28:55 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[martie]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=969</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In development/economics the M4P doughnut is a commonly used tool to analyse and present market systems. Unfortunately, no website or software exists to build these ""donuts"" and they are respectively built inconsistently/with poor designs, etc. </p>
<p>I would like to build a drag and drop builder that would be hosted on a website for this purpose. Users will be able to build and download there donut on the website. The website must have some way of ensuring font consistency (if you read the job description, please add ""9784"" for question two), symetrics and allow uses to edit, save and go back to past designs (e.g. login system required). </p>
<p>I assume this job description will change slightly upon conversation with shortlisted candidates and the scope of the workload.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>CRM for Customer Support Department</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/crm-for-customer-support-department/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 06:02:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[roswell]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=980</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi We need a basic application designed to handle the following Operation:</p>
<p>1. Customer calls at our Support Phone Number, the phone automatically disconnects and sends a sms to the customer saying ""Thank you for connecting with us, our Support Executive will call you shortly""</p>
<p>2. The Phone number and Time of the call is automatically reflected on our Application Dashboard. </p>
<p>3. Our Support Executive can call to that Customer's Number through his Desktop using our application.The application records the day and time of the call.</p>
<p>4. After resolving the Customer's issue, our Support Executive can fill a brief detail about the conversation/issue.</p>
<p>5. Since my customers are from multiple countries therefore,Cloud Telephony/VOIP integration may be required.</p>
<p>There will be various types of logs &amp; reports that will reflect on the reporting section of this application, but that is secondary in nature. I need a crisp &amp; simple application which everyone can use.</p>
<p>Freelancers with previous experience in developing such applications will be preferred.I am open to Open Source Solutions as long as it solves my purpose,feel free to ask if you have any questions.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Virtual Assistant / Organizing &#038; Downloading</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/virtual-assistant-organizing-downloading/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 08:02:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[roswell]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=987</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We need a virtual assistance to help search, organize, and download images, photos, or videos for a large collage project.</p>
<p>There are 3 types of project:</p>
<p>A. Download 100 images/photos and 900 videos</p>
<p>B. Download 200 images/photos and 800 videos</p>
<p>C. Download 300 images/photos and 700 videos</p>
<p>Please indicate your project preference if any. You maybe assigned one based on what is needed. You will be given access to an app/software to help with downloading and making the whole process a lot easier.</p>
<p>Photos and videos needs to be HD quality.</p>
<p>This is a very straight forward task</p>
<p>1. Search the web</p>
<p>2. Pick A or B or C</p>
<p>3. Organize in folders and label them in excel. The labeling will need details and description of the image/video. You can cut and paste from where you obtain the source.</p>
<p>4. Upload to the cloud.</p>
<p>Must be English fluent so we can communicate well and efficiently.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Find an Accountant</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/find-an-accountant/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 08:02:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[devenwestley]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=999</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We need to make the book keeping, accounting and audit for a limited liability company, for the years 2010 to 2015, all inclusive.</p>
<p>The vouchers are organized in chronological order, and organized well in box files, and numbered consecutively. </p>
<p>We need the usual work done, with NSSF, NHIF, Trial balance, financial statement.</p>
<p>We have bank statements for most of all years in total, we may be missing only a few bank statements for a few months.</p>
<p>We have all cheque sleeves.</p>
<p>A big chunk of the entire book keeping has been done already.</p>
<p>All entries has been done via ETR machine.</p>
<p>Bank reconciliation must be done too, for accuracy purposes.</p>
<p>We do explicitly not need anything to be done on tax. Simply follow tax laws, that is all. </p>
<p>The work will take place at our location.</p>
<p>You will be engaged on usual professional terms and conditions. The bid sum is based on all 6 years, however, we will create a milestone for each year.</p>
<p>We need that you quote (bid) for the total work, which shall include accounting and audit from the point where we provide for you the vouchers, up to the point where we have an annual financial statement.</p>
<p>In terms of accounting method, use the simplest possible method. </p>
<p>IN the period between 2014 and 2016, there has been no activity, therefore, we expect it to be a question about doing a few operations.</p>
<p>Questions are welcome. </p>
<p>If you intend to bid above USD 3,000 for the total work of doing these 6 years, then do not waste your time.</p>
<p>Foreigners should not bid on the task. We need a local from Kenya to bid, as you would need to go through the material.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Game Environment Presentation</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/game-environment-presentation/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Sep 2016 07:16:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kermitlawrence]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=1006</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Read the project description and instructions below. Go through the attached files. </p>
<p>NOTE: This work needs to be done within 24 hours.</p>
<p>Game Environment Presentation </p>
<p>Shooting bullet exercise: Using a 3rd person controller, apply bullet scripts and physics to a character in a designed environment.</p>
<p>PART I – Setup the environment:</p>
<p>Create a new project for Unity, choose to import the “Character Controller” assets. Create Models, Textures, and Scripts folders and import the yurtmodel and textures in to the associated folders.</p>
<p>Place the model into the Hierarchy, create a point light and adjust the setting so the environment is visible.</p>
<p>Fix the “Object02” &amp; “Object07”model by re-link the texture and choose the transparent materials. </p>
<p>Create a gameobject cube, scale the cube to the size of the floor to place it by the floor. Turn off the “Mesh Renderer” for the cube. This will serve as a collider for the character to walk on.</p>
<p>Drag the 3rd Person controller into the scene(Characters &gt; ThirdPersonCharacter &gt; Prefabs &gt; ThirdPersonController). Adjust the size of the character and place it above the ground. Make the main camera the child of the 3rd Person controller and drag the main camera behind him, test the scene.</p>
<p>Create mesh colliders for the steps and table geometry by adding the components to the selected objects, choose physics &gt; Mesh Colliders. Test the scene.</p>
<p>PART II – Create shooting bullets: </p>
<p>Create empty gameobject and rename your empty game object gun.</p>
<p>Drag the gun on top of your 3rd person controller, place it roughly by the hand.</p>
<p>Create a sphere game object , resize and reposition it close to the gun.</p>
<p>Add a rigidbody to the sphere by going to component &gt; physics &gt; rigidbody.</p>
<p>Create a “Weapon” folder in the Project.</p>
<p>Right click on folder and create a prefab, name the prefab “bullet”. Drag the sphere (from step 4) on to prefab.</p>
<p>Delete bullet from scene it is no longer needed.</p>
<p>Drag the “shoot” script into weapon folder.</p>
<p>Attach shoot script to “gun”, the empty game object.</p>
<p>Drag bullet rigidbody on to projectile section of shoot script.</p>
<p>Test the scene.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>OEM RF Module to Raspberry PI</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/oem-rf-module-to-raspberry-pi/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 12 Sep 2016 06:19:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[hanagim]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=1011</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I am wanting to integrate an 900 mhz OEM RF Module with a Raspberry PI.</p>
<p>The OEM RF Module must be bridged with the ethernet port in the Raspberry PI.</p>
<p>The OEM RF Module has available to it several modulation, speed, and payload settings that need to be made available to users as configurable options via a web server on the raspberry PI.</p>
<p>The OEM Module will come with an API to interface with the Raspberry PI and interfaces via  TTL via 24pin Samtec Connector.</p>
<p>First portion of the job will be to consult on the design of the interface both Hardware and Software.</p>
<p>Successful completion of the project will be a working 900mhz ethernet radio using the PI board interfaced with the OEM RF Module, that is configurable by users via web server hosted on the PI.</p>
<p>Other improvements will be included after successful delivery of the radio.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Develop a WordPress plugin</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/develop-a-wordpress-plugin/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:04:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[pearcedenny]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=838</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I need a developer who can create an add on plugin for the beaver builder Wordpress page builder. It should be extremely light weight and clean code. Here is a description of what is needed in the plugin, etc.</p>
<p>As of now when someone uses the beaver builder to create or edit a page in Wordpress, users have the ability to change and edit all aspects of a page. They can change font sizes, margins, paddings, weights, etc... I need a plugin that limits an "editor role" to only change text, pictures and colors. All other aspects of the page builder should not be editable by an editor role. Everything should remain unchanged for an administration role though. </p>
<p>Please provide your bid and timeline for completion if you are interested and are very sure you can accomplish this task to the highest quality.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I am looking for someone who can proof-read and edit professionally. The book I have is getting itself ready for a 2nd print. The 1st print was in 2012. I require the person to have great command of english. The book are written using American English.</p>

<p>The book is written with the general reader in mind. Not looking for formal reading or academic ones. but must be reader-friendly. This is a A5 book containing approximately 30,000 to 34,000 words.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>I would like to hire a WordPress Developer</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/i-would-like-to-hire-a-wordpress-developer/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:04:17 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[dorisclarke]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=973</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We have recently launched a new WordPress site, with a linked WooCommerce paid online membership side. On the paid membership side, we have lots of downloadable content and it's difficult for a user to find the content relevant to what they're looking for. </p>
<p>We therefore would like to do the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Add a search field </li>
<li>Add multiple filters, approximately 4 altogether. We would therefore assign multiple categories to a download so that the user can use multiple filters to find what they need. The user could use just 1 filter, or all 4.</li>
<li>Potentially add pagination.</li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Dubai &#038; Gulf Blog Articles</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/dubai-gulf-blog-articles/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:14:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=782</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I’m looking for someone based in the UAE to write weekly articles for a recruitment blog.</p>
<p>The articles will cover topics on topics such as:</p>
<p>1. How to land a job in the oil and gas industry</p>
<p>2. Insights into the Dubai job market </p>
<p>3. Dubai Media City – an insight into companies and activity</p>
<p>You can refer to third party reports but the content must be 100% unique.</p>
<p>We’re looking for articles that are around 800 to 1000 words.</p>
<p>Is this something you can help with?</p>
<p>Looking forward to hearing back from you.</p>
<p>Best regards,</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Battery Management System Design</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/battery-management-system-design__trashed/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 01 Sep 2016 07:55:02 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[hanagim]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=797</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[The goal of this project is to find a talented individual to design a BMS and provide a functional unit, as well as a BOM, and schematics.

The device is a battery powered heating coil

The specifications:
<ul>
 	<li>The load circuit has a low impedance, of about 0.8 to 1.3 Ω, it is a small nichrome  heating coil</li>
 	<li>Open circuit voltage output around 12 V/ The voltage output may not be constant due to the low resistance, and will rather have a wide range once connected to a load</li>
 	<li>Higher than normal power is needed between 10-30W</li>
 	<li>The battery would provide high currents to reach the required power rating, usually 1- 6A to heat the coil</li>
 	<li>Rechargeable battery has to be able to withstand low resistance</li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Data Cleaner</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/data-cleaner/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:07:55 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=876</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hello!</p>
<p>We are looking for one person who will check our contact database and do everything needed to make it accurate and correct.  With 20k records, the task will take commitment and dedication.</p>
<p>It is a very simple task, however it is repetitive.</p>
<p>You will look at each record, check for missing fields such as email address and find them by calling the contact to ask for the data.  You will also correct any errors in the data such as multiple contacts with same email or same address.</p>
<p>You must have great spoken and written English as you will be making phone calls as well as sending emails.</p>
<p>This is very basic work and we will hire the most cost effective person who we believe can do a reliable job.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I would like to create an APP as a tourist guide in cities. I would like to integrate the camera feature in the APP, so I would be able to take pictures while I'm following the track and use it as a checklist of places in order to know if i have achieved the expectations on my trip. I would like to set/add/modify/update places easily.</p>
<p>Thank you in advance.</p>

	<item>
		<title>Write an Android application</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/write-an-android-application/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:04:49 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kristycarey]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=985</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Android quiz app for student’s exam revision.</p>
<p>Features:</p>
<ol>
<li>Instant scoring and ranking with a leader-board: Students are challenged to do better when they see their current scores and ranks as well as that of their peers.</li>
<li>Social based learning: Students can challenge each other on social media to become top student in different subjects. Students can also invite friends and challenge friends to take same quiz.</li>
<li>Recognition and incentives: Top performing students are rewarded weekly.</li>
<li>Geographical mapping: Tied to the leader board, students can see where top students come from.</li>
<li>In app purchases </li>
</ol>
<p>NOTE: I should be able to add questions and answers to the app anytime.</p>
<p>Expectations:</p>
<p>I will own the full source code, app and all copyrights etc.</p>
<p>The source code will be well documented.</p>
<p>The architecture must allow for future addition of new APIs.</p>
<p>The app should work on all android versions and systems including tablets.</p>
<p>The system design should be flexible </p>
<p>Developer is an end-to-end solutions provider. </p>
<p>All testing will be 100% your responsibility. Bugs and other compatibility problems found after releasing will be your responsibility.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Email Marketing Server with Interspire</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/email-marketing-server-with-interspire/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:05:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[lyndon]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=1009</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I need an email server setup with Interspire for bulk marketing to a clean list. Hard bounces under 1% on this list.</p>
<p>I recently hired a vendor for this task. Please read so you do not make these same mistakes. The vendor rented a VPS which was too slow for this task. I received constant error messages because the server was too slow to process the task. The vendor also did not use enough IP addresses, so the soft bounce rate was very high, even though my content has a zero spam score. </p>
<p>Your job will be to setup the server, install Interspire and monitor the performance of the server. You will deal with any spam complaints and rotate enough IPs to ensure delivery. My content is business related. I will load lists and manage all content. </p>
<p>I will pay with two milestones; one when the server is available to me and properly working, and the second milestone after 30 days. I will not release the second milestone unless the work is completed to my satisfaction. If you demonstrate competency, I will have many ongoing projects for you.</p>
<p>Only reply if you are an expert on Interspire.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>WordPress Plugins For Gravatars, Authors and Tweets</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/wordpress-plugins-for-gravatars-authors-and-tweets/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:15:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[dorisclarke]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=1027</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Job 1: I have a WordPress site where a lot of users make comments. However, many users don’t have a gravatar image. I want to encourage all users to set up a gravatar image. I would like a pop up that appears every 14 days to logged in users only who don’t have a gravatar image. The pop up is to remind them to get one with instructions on how to get one.

Job 2: I currently use the WordPress plugin Fancier Author Box. I want to get rid of it because:
<ol>
 	<li>I don’t like the way it loads via JS, it should load in the HTML</li>
 	<li>I often have multiple authors for a document. Fancier Author Box does not detect multiple authors.</li>
</ol>
To set up multiple authors, I use Co-Authors Plus plugin.

I would like code developing that adds a HTML Author box to the foot of each post. You can do this by creating code for my functions.php, or by creating your own plugin. I would like each Author to have their own box. Each box should have the same layout as I currently enjoy. Here are some details of the https://vip.wordpress.com/documentation/incorporate-co-authors-plus-template-tags-into-your-theme/

I would also like two new shortcodes creating. A shortcode for “All Authors” and a short code of “All Editors”. It is for display on an “about” page. A writer must be an author on an article in the last 12 months to be on either list.

Job 3: The problem with showing / embedding tweets in posts is:
<ol>
 	<li>Loading lazily pushes the page down. This is after the page has rendered. So if a user opens a comment, the comment then jumps from view on screen because the tweets loading higher up the page.</li>
 	<li>The tweet box are always right aligned, so looks untidy.</li>
</ol>
Please add some CSS to my child theme so that Tweets are always centred in an article and so that room is left for the tweet.

Notes: I prefer coders who ask questions, and good standards must be followed. I currently use php 5.6 but want to upgrade to php 7, so you code must work with both php 5.6 and 7. Good design and code standards are a minimum requirement.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Counseling Appointment Request System</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/counseling-appointment-request-system-2__trashed/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:04:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[nikolaospachis]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=780</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>You will be making an online counseling appointment request system. There are 3 roles in the application namely counselor, student, admin. All the roles should be validated using passwords stored in a database. The passwords can be stored in the database in hash - MD5/SHA1/SHA2.</p>
<p>All 3 of them share a common login screen. Depending on the role the next page should vary.</p>
<p>Student should be able to login to the system and schedule an appointment on a date selected from the calendar. Once the student submits his appointment request, it should get updated into the DB. When a counsellor sees that request he should be able to approve or reject the request. The admin should be able to see the database in a page. He should not be able to edit any of the values though.</p>
<p>You have to use C# ASP.NET with MVC using Entity framework for this project. You can use Visual studio to complete this task.</p>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>CAD for Physical Product for Molding</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/cad-for-physical-product-for-molding__trashed/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:04:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[trinebritta]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=831</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We are looking for an experienced CAD who has previously designed products for molding.</p>
<p>The product we want designed is a simple plastic handle for a popular drinking mug.</p>
<p>We will want to make a different design, but that is the general idea.</p>
<p>We are going to get the design 3-D printed and eventually manufactured for production, so we will need a STEP file once completed.</p>
<p>We will provide a rough sketch/drawing of what we want the handle to look like once hired.</p>
<p>In your response, please state your previous experience designing products for molding, and an estimate of how many hours you think this will take to complete.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Asian Movie News Content Writer Required</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/asian-movie-news-content-writer-required__trashed/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 12 Sep 2016 06:18:55 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[hatruong]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=907</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We are currently looking out for content writers with a passion for Asian movies /Dramas (Hong Kong, Chinese, Japanese, Korean and more).</p>
<p>Even those with little experience within the Asian Movie industry are still eligible for this role as long as you have a love for movies and a passion for writing.</p>
<p>The Job requires primarily re-writing press releases for display on the website.</p>
<p>The Job also requires researching the Hot topics in the asian Movie Entertainment industry and rewriting any content found within our 'Wordpress' based blog system.</p>
<p>You will not be required to supply any images with your posts as we will do this for you. (But those who are able to re-size images and upload to our system would be a bonus)</p>
<p>WordPress knowledge a huge bonus!</p>
<p>Note: Budget is for the initial writing of 10 short articles (250 words approx).</p>
<p>A sound understanding of wordpress and creating posts is desirable but not essential.</p>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Clothing Manufacturer Needed</title>
		<link>https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/project/clothing-manufacturer-needed__trashed/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 26 Oct 2016 07:04:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[nancypauletta]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://freelanceengine.enginethemes.com/?post_type=project&#038;p=915</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I am starting a new clothing line, and have about 10-12 clothing pieces that I need produced/manufactured. I have flat drawings of each, with some notes on measurements.</p>
<p>In total I will need 40 of each item. (10 in each size S-XL)</p>
<p>These pieces are men's and women's. </p>
<p>I will need a sample of each, which I will pay an extra amount for, before going into production. For the final products I will be sourcing the fabric myself, but for the samples I will be ok with fabrics that are close to the final pieces.</p>
<p>If all goes well with this first round, I will be looking for a long term manufacturer with much larger quantities.</p>]]></content:encoded>
